Explore retina data.frame using base R

Frederick J Tan

23 August 2021

Load packages

library( "readr" )

Load data

df <- read_tsv( "retina.tsv" )
df

Subset rows

roi <- df$cell_type == "retinal rod cell"
class( roi )
[1] "logical"
length( roi )
[1] 8217
head( roi )
[1] FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE FALSE
table( roi )
roi
FALSE  TRUE 
 6627  1590 
df_rod <- df[roi,]
df_rod
dim( df_rod )
[1] 1590   18

Visualize enrichment

hist( df_rod$RHO )

hist( df$RHO )

hist( df_rod$PDE6H )

hist( df$PDE6H )

Scatterplot

plot( df$UMAP_1, df$UMAP_2 )

plot( df$UMAP_1, df$UMAP_2 )
points( df_rod$UMAP_1, df_rod$UMAP_2, col="red" )

Exercises

  • Create a scatterplot with three cell types highlighted with different colors
  • For three other genes, identify in which cell_types each is enriched
  • Which gene has the highest variation?
